Feedback
--------

If you are interested in the FAIL project, please subscribe its
https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/fail-users[mailing list].
This list is for users and developers.
Once you subscribe, you can post comments, ideas and questions about FAIL.

Use http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?group_id=258474[tracker]
to submit bug reports, feature requests and small code patches.

History
-------

FAIL 1.0.2 (2011-04-??)::

Fixed decoding of ILC, AP3, RIP, PIC, CPR and 16012-byte HIP.
Added support for the MCH, 256 and IGE formats.
Added Windows thumbnail provider.
Fixed compilation errors with the new libpng.
Moved source code from SVN to Git.

FAIL 1.0.1 (2010-08-25)::

Windows setup has been created. A coder for ImageMagick has been created.
MCP, GHG and HR2 formats are supported. Build process has been improved.

FAIL 1.0.0 (2009-08-25)::

Initial release.

